- always use tabs for indent
- whenever any font, image or audio asset is added, it must be added to the list of files on the loading screen
- all CSS should be placed within ./src/styles/App.css
- CSS should be nested to mimic the hierarchy of HTML elements when possible
- css psuedo elements or states should be nested if the parent css exists
- When nesting an element selector (like div, p, span, button, etc.) that does not have a class name, you must put "& " before the element name.
- Do not use the CSS properties transition, opacity, or border-radius
- Add tooltips to interactive elements when appropriate


